<subSubSection id="C34F079DFFD9ED46FF56FEE4FA25FE36" pageId="5" pageNumber="394" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BEA5416FFD9ED46FF56FEE4FB96FED9" blockId="5.[151,1437,258,394]" box="[199,1066,331,358]" pageId="5" pageNumber="394">
<emphasis id="B9218804FFD9ED46FF56FEE4FEF2FEDA" bold="true" box="[199,334,331,357]" pageId="5" pageNumber="394">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named after the 
<typeStatus id="54EEEAB4FFD9ED46FD3CFEE3FD61FED9" box="[685,733,332,358]" pageId="5" pageNumber="394">type</typeStatus>
locality (noun in apposition).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA5416FFD9ED46FF56FEC0FA25FE36" blockId="5.[151,1437,258,394]" box="[199,1433,367,394]" pageId="5" pageNumber="394">
<emphasis id="B9218804FFD9ED46FF56FEC0FE13FE36" bold="true" box="[199,431,367,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="394">Generic placement.</emphasis>
This new species is placed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C552F95FFD9ED46FC93FEC0FCC0FE36" authorityName="L. Koch" authorityYear="1872" box="[770,892,367,393]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Carepalxis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9218804FFD9ED46FC93FEC0FCC0FE36" box="[770,892,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="394">Carepalxis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
primarily because of its pair of cephalic humps.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF2A049EFFD9ED46FF06F8E9FACCF83D" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5824332" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5824332" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5824332/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="394" startId="5.[151,264,1862,1886]" targetBox="[178,1417,449,1824]" targetPageId="5">
