<subSubSection id="C34F079DFFD9ED45FF56F87AFC7FFE6E" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="395" pageId="5" pageNumber="394" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BEA5416FFD9ED45FF56F87AFC7FFE6E" blockId="5.[199,1436,2005,2031]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,1077]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="395" pageId="5" pageNumber="394">
<emphasis id="B9218804FFD9ED46FF56F87AFEFEF850" bold="true" box="[199,322,2005,2031]" pageId="5" pageNumber="394">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Its overall morphology is closer to 
<taxonomicName id="4C552F95FFD9ED46FD2FF87AFBC3F850" authority="Mello-Leitao" authorityName="Mello-Leitao" box="[702,1151,2005,2031]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Ocrepeira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mastophoroides">
<emphasis id="B9218804FFD9ED46FD2FF87AFC5BF850" box="[702,999,2005,2031]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="394">Ocrepeira mastophoroides</emphasis>
Mello-Leitão
</taxonomicName>
than any other 
<taxonomicName id="4C552F95FFD9ED45FAB3F87AFF4CFF0E" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Carepalxis" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="395" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B9218804FFD9ED46FAB3F87AFA20F850" box="[1314,1436,2005,2031]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="394">Carepalxis</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
It differs by the presence of a large pair of cephalic humps, as delimited by the genus diagnosis. It has five pairs of tubercles instead of six. The epigynum is different by its Y-shaped scape and the bilobed margins of the lateral plates. The longitudinal groove in 
<taxonomicName id="4C552F95FFDAED45FDCEFF70FC8EFF46" box="[607,818,223,249]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Ocrepeira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="395" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mastophoroides">
<emphasis id="B9218804FFDAED45FDCEFF70FC8EFF46" box="[607,818,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">O. mastophoroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to the tip of the scape, in 
<taxonomicName id="4C552F95FFDAED45FB40FF70FAFFFF47" authority="Ferreira-Sousa &amp; Motta, 2022" authorityName="Ferreira-Sousa &amp; Motta" authorityYear="2022" box="[1233,1347,223,249]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Carepalxis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="395" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="topazio" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B9218804FFDAED45FB40FF70FAFFFF47" box="[1233,1347,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">C. topazio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9218804FFDAED45FAD8FF70FA3AFF46" bold="true" box="[1353,1414,223,249]" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A212357FFFDAED45FAD8FF70FA3AFF46" box="[1353,1414,223,249]" pageId="6" pageNumber="395" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
it goes from the tip to about half of the scape. Additionally, the height of clypeus equals twice the height of an anterior median eye, instead of the same size of this eye as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C552F95FFDAED45FD7EFE88FC7FFEFE" box="[751,963,295,321]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Ocrepeira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="395" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mastophoroides">
<emphasis id="B9218804FFDAED45FD7EFE88FC7FFEFE" box="[751,963,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">O. mastophoroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C552F95FFDAED45FC40FE88FB18FEFF" authority="Ferreira-Sousa &amp; Motta, 2022" authorityName="Ferreira-Sousa &amp; Motta" authorityYear="2022" box="[977,1188,295,321]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Carepalxis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="395" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="topazio" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B9218804FFDAED45FC40FE88FB18FEFF" box="[977,1188,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">Carepalxis topazio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9218804FFDAED45FB3DFE88FB57FEFE" bold="true" box="[1196,1259,295,321]" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A212357FFFDAED45FB3DFE88FB57FEFE" box="[1196,1259,295,321]" pageId="6" pageNumber="395" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is distinct from 
<emphasis id="B9218804FFDAED45FF06FEE4FE58FEDA" box="[151,484,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">
<taxonomicName id="4C552F95FFDAED45FF06FEE4FE86FEDA" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1895" box="[151,314,331,357]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Carepalxis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="395" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salobrensis">C. salobrensis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C552F95FFDAED45FED6FEE4FE58FEDA" authority="Ferreira-Sousa &amp; Motta, 2022" authorityName="Ferreira-Sousa &amp; Motta" authorityYear="2022" box="[327,484,331,357]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Carepalxis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="395" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quasimodo" status="n. sp.">C. quasimodo</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B9218804FFDAED45FE7DFEE4FD97FEDA" bold="true" box="[492,555,331,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A212357FFFDAED45FE7DFEE4FD97FEDA" box="[492,555,331,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="395" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C552F95FFDAED45FDF4FEE4FD5EFEDA" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1895" box="[613,738,331,357]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Carepalxis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="395" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="camelus">
<emphasis id="B9218804FFDAED45FDF4FEE4FD5EFEDA" box="[613,738,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">C. camelus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of abdominal lateral tubercles (
<figureCitation id="136E4893FFDAED45FA95FEE4FA32FEDA" box="[1284,1422,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1862,1886]" captionTargetBox="[178,1417,449,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-78@5.[151,1435,417,1839]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. Carepalxis topazio n. sp. 16–18, Epigynum (16, ventral; 17, lateral; 18, posterior). 19–21, Female habitus (19, dorsal; 20, frontal; 21, lateral). Voucher: 16–21, (DZUB 8699). Scale bars: genitalia, 0.25 mm; other drawings, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5824332" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5824332/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">Figs. 19, 21</figureCitation>
), but lacks the posterior median tubercles present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C552F95FFDAED45FD4BFEC0FCE9FE37" box="[730,853,367,393]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Carepalxis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="395" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perpera">
<emphasis id="B9218804FFDAED45FD4BFEC0FD51FE36" box="[730,749,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9218804FFDAED45FD6DFEC0FCE9FE37" box="[764,853,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">perpera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The epigynum has a long scape (
<figureCitation id="136E4893FFDAED45FB4BFEC0FAD8FE36" box="[1242,1380,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1862,1886]" captionTargetBox="[178,1417,449,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-78@5.[151,1435,417,1839]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. Carepalxis topazio n. sp. 16–18, Epigynum (16, ventral; 17, lateral; 18, posterior). 19–21, Female habitus (19, dorsal; 20, frontal; 21, lateral). Voucher: 16–21, (DZUB 8699). Scale bars: genitalia, 0.25 mm; other drawings, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5824332" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5824332/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">Figs. 16, 17</figureCitation>
), the inner borders of the lateral plates forms a heart shape around the posterior median plate (
<figureCitation id="136E4893FFDAED45FBFEFE3CFB7CFE12" box="[1135,1216,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1862,1886]" captionTargetBox="[178,1417,449,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-78@5.[151,1435,417,1839]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. Carepalxis topazio n. sp. 16–18, Epigynum (16, ventral; 17, lateral; 18, posterior). 19–21, Female habitus (19, dorsal; 20, frontal; 21, lateral). Voucher: 16–21, (DZUB 8699). Scale bars: genitalia, 0.25 mm; other drawings, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5824332" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5824332/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
), unlike the median plates of 
<taxonomicName id="4C552F95FFDAED45FF6FFE18FEC6FE6E" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1895" box="[254,378,439,465]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Carepalxis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="395" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="camelus">
<emphasis id="B9218804FFDAED45FF6FFE18FEC6FE6E" box="[254,378,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">C. camelus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C552F95FFDAED45FE20FE18FDF0FE6E" authority="Ferreira-Sousa &amp; Motta, 2022" authorityName="Ferreira-Sousa &amp; Motta" authorityYear="2022" box="[433,588,439,465]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Carepalxis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="395" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quasimodo" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B9218804FFDAED45FE20FE18FDF0FE6E" box="[433,588,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">C. quasimodo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9218804FFDAED45FDC2FE18FD2EFE6E" bold="true" box="[595,658,439,465]" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A212357FFFDAED45FDC2FE18FD2EFE6E" box="[595,658,439,465]" pageId="6" pageNumber="395" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, which are hidden (
<figureCitation id="136E4893FFDAED45FCE1FE18FC0EFE6E" box="[880,946,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[211,1372,217,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-21@3.[203,1385,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Carepalxis quasimodo n. sp. 1–5, Epigynum (1, posterior; 1 ventral; 3, lateral; 4, ventral without scape; 5, posterior, cleared). 6–10, Female habitus; 6–8, female from Brasília (6, dorsal; 7, lateral; 8, frontal); 9–10, female from Jaborandi (9, dorsal; 10 lateral)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5824326" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5824326/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34F079DFFDAED45FF56FE75FE34FC52" pageId="6" pageNumber="395" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEA5416FFDAED45FF56FE75FDC6FC76" blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1077]" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">
<emphasis id="B9218804FFDAED45FF56FE75FEE5FE4B" bold="true" box="[199,345,474,500]" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B9218804FFDAED45FEF2FE74FC74FE4A" box="[355,968,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">
Female 
<typeStatus id="54EEEAB4FFDAED45FE50FE74FD9DFE4A" box="[449,545,475,501]" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">holotype</typeStatus>
from Serra dos Topázios, Cristalina
</emphasis>
. Total length 8.83. Carapace: 3.98 long, 2.54 wide, cephalic humps 2.07 high, thoracic region 1.27 high. Cephalic region redish-brown, humps covered with short white setae, thoracic region glabrous, orange-cream. Clypeus: 0.40. Chelicerae: redish-brown with an arched dark stripe and many setae near to the clypeus, fangs dark red. Eye diameters: AME 0.18, ALE 0.09, PME 0.14, PLE 0.13. Eye interdistances: AME–AME 0.22, AME–ALE 0.72, PME–PME 0.46, PME–PLE 0.87, AME–PME 0.21. Endites: 0.99 long, 0.74 wide, redish-brown, yellow from the half to the median edges. Labium: 0.62 long, 0.77 wide, same color pattern as endites. Sternum: 1.36 long, 1.59 wide, orange with numerous setae on anterior margin. Legs: dark orange with irregular redish-brown spots and rings. Leg formula 1 2 4 3. Measures: L1. Femur 3.36, patella 1.76, tibia 2.31, metatarsus 2.32, tarsus 0.78 / L2. Femur 3.26, patella 1.49, tibia 2.14, metatarsus 2.29, tarsus 0.85 / L3. Femur 2.23, patella 1.25, tibia 1.34, metatarsus 1.07, tarsus 0.74 / L4. Femur 3.38, patella 1.70, tibia 2.02, metatarsus 2.01, tarsus 0.72/ Pedipalp. Femur 1.08, patella 0.62, tibia 0.74, tarsus 1.30. Abdomen: 7.71 long, 7.25 wide, 4.60 high. Abdomen round, greyish-orange, dorsaly with a pair of anterior dark tubercles and four pairs of lateral grey tubercles. In lateral view, the abdomen has a wavy black line on each side. The venter has a big grey area between the epigynum and spinnerets.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA5416FFDAED45FF56FC7CFE34FC52" blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1077]" box="[199,392,979,1005]" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">
<emphasis id="B9218804FFDAED45FF56FC7CFEB7FC52" bold="true" box="[199,267,979,1005]" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34F079DFFDAED45FF56FC59FCD6FB8A" pageId="6" pageNumber="395" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BEA5416FFDAED45FF56FC59FCD6FB8A" blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1077]" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">
<emphasis id="B9218804FFDAED45FF56FC59FDECFBAF" bold="true" box="[199,592,1014,1041]" pageId="6" pageNumber="395">Distribution and natural history.</emphasis>
The only known specimen was collected by beating sheet during the early rainy season in Brazilian Cerrado, in a rocky savanna formation.
</paragraph>
